 as tailings—engages with human and non-human entities in multiple ways through a process the authors call geosymbiosis. Some of these geosymbioses result in toxicity and damage, while others become the basis of lively novel ecologies. A particular kind of power emerges in the process, one that is radically indifferent to human beings but that affects them in many ways. Learning to live with geosymbioses offers a tentative path forward amid ongoing environmental devastation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCopper mines and miningxEnvironmental aspectszChile. 0aHuman ecologyzChile. 0aWaterxPollutionzChilezCarén Reservoir Region. 0aWaterxPollutionzChilezCarén Reservoir Region. 7aSCIENCE / Environmental Science (see also Chemistry / Environmental).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2022 Englishz978311099344808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2022z9783110993219oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520386303?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520386303423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520386303/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099344-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb20